Description: A tall, situla-shaped jar of coarse red-brown sitware pottery, with a rounded base. The exterior was covered by a red slip, but most of this has flaked off. At the top there is a cylindrical neck with a plain rim. The micaceous fabric contains many inclusions of grit, mostly small pieces of limestone or chert.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, Findspot 50, domestic buildings in the urban area to the east of the Saite enclosure (so-called "Camp").
Curator's comments: The Findspot number 50 has been scratched on the item. See also London, PM, UC 19251.
